# Cursor Rules

## Read First
Before starting any task, read:
- `.agent/lessons.md` — hard-won lessons from past sessions
- `.agent/session-handoff.md` — context from the last session
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — system architecture (if it exists)

## Git Rules (Non-Negotiable)
- NEVER commit to `main` or `master`. Always use feature branches.
- Branch naming: `<type>/<short-description>` (feat/, fix/, refactor/, chore/, docs/, test/)
- Conventional commits: `type(scope): description`
- Atomic commits — one logical change each.
- Run tests and linting before pushing.
- Never commit secrets, tokens, or credentials.
- Never force-push to shared branches.
- Never disable tests to make them pass.

## Team Protocol (if `.agent/team/` exists)
- On startup: read `.agent/team/` files (registry, board, messages, locks). Register if not already. Update heartbeat.
- Agent ID format: `<tool>-<n>` (e.g., `claude-1`, `cursor-2`)
- Branch naming in team mode: `<type>/<agent-id>/<description>` (e.g., `feat/claude-1/auth-flow`)
- Before starting work: sync team files, check board for tasks, check locks for conflicts, claim task and acquire locks, post a message.
- During work: update heartbeat each commit, respect locks, coordinate via messages if you need locked files.
- Advisory locks: check `.agent/team/locks.md` before modifying files. Don't touch paths locked by active agents.
- Conflict resolution: post a message and coordinate — never force-resolve conflicts with other agents.
- Session end: release locks, update board, move to Inactive in registry, post summary message, write handoff.
- Stale agents (heartbeat >30 min): any agent may clean up their locks, release their tasks, move to Inactive.
- Team commands: `/team-join`, `/team-status`, `/team-claim`, `/team-sync`, `/team-handoff`

## Autonomy Model
PROCEED autonomously if work is reversible: new files, new branches, additive changes, running tests.
ASK PERMISSION (with context + risks) for: operations on main, deleting pre-existing files, modifying CI/CD, changing env vars, DB migrations, external API calls with side effects, installing production deps.
Format permission requests as:
```
⚠️ PERMISSION REQUIRED
Action: [what]
Why: [reason]
Risk: [what could go wrong]
Reversible: [yes/no]
```

## Task Pattern
1. Understand — read code and context before acting
2. Plan — state approach before coding; write `.agent/current-plan.md` for complex tasks
3. Implement — on a feature branch, atomic commits
4. Verify — run tests, review your own diff
5. Document — update relevant docs and inline comments (explain *why*, not *what*)
6. Handoff — update `.agent/session-handoff.md` at end of session

## Documentation
- Update README.md if you change setup/run/deploy steps
- Update docs/ARCHITECTURE.md if you add/change major components
- Fix stale docs when you find them
- At END of every session, update `.agent/session-handoff.md` with: what was done, current state (branch, tests, build), what's next, open questions, gotchas

## Learning
When something goes wrong, append to `.agent/lessons.md`:
- What happened
- Root cause
- What should have been done
- A concrete rule to prevent recurrence

## Error Recovery
1. Stop — don't compound errors
2. Assess blast radius
3. Revert to known good state if possible
4. Inform user if break affects anything outside your branch
5. Document in lessons.md
6. Fix with clear root cause understanding
